{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_0196ZX4yELjHgY2V1ZePuuH3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I've applied the remediation. Here's a summary of my analysis and the fix.\n\n## What FINDING.txt described\nA CWE-200 Information Exposure vulnerability in `Redirect30xInterceptor.java`, spanning the header-name imports (41-46), the credential-strip decision in `exitAfterHandlingRedirect` (113-119), and the header-removal block in `propagatedHeaders` (209-216).\n\n## What I verified\nI traced the full redirect data flow exhaustively (the interceptor, `Uri.isSameBase`, `NettyRequestSender`, `NettyRequestFactory`, `NettyResponseFuture`):\n\n- `stripAuth = !sameBase || schemeDowngrade || stripAuthorizationOnRedirect` is `true` for **every** cross-origin or scheme-downgrade redirect.\n- When stripping, the code removes the `Authorization` and `Proxy-Authorization` headers in `propagatedHeaders`, nulls the realm on the new `RequestBuilder`, and nulls `future.setRealm(null)`/`future.setProxyRealm(null)` — so realm-based credential regeneration in `NettyRequestFactory` is also prevented.\n\nThat credential path is sound — it can only over-strip, never leak. The residual gap is that `propagatedHeaders` copies **all other** request headers to the redirect target, and the one credential-bearing header it failed to remove is **`Cookie`**. On a cross-origin or HTTPS→HTTP downgrade redirect, a request's `Cookie` header (session credentials) was forwarded to the new target — the CWE-200 exposure, in exactly the flagged regions.\n\n## The fix\nIn `propagatedHeaders`, when `stripAuthorization` is set (cross-origin / scheme-downgrade / configured), the `Cookie` header is now removed alongside `Authorization`/`Proxy-Authorization`, plus the `COOKIE` header-name import.\n\n## Why behavior is preserved\n- **Same-origin** redirects (`stripAuthorization == false`) are untouched — cookies and auth still flow as before.\n- Cookies legitimately scoped to the **new** target are still attached afterward via the `CookieStore` lookup (`cookieStore.get(newUri)` → re-encoded at write time), so only the leaked, cross-origin-inherited `Cookie` header is dropped.\n- Existing redirect tests are same-origin, and cookie tests use `addCookie` (which flows through `request.getCookies()`, not the raw header), so none are affected.\n\nNo build/commit was performed (offline maven can't resolve dependencies here), and changes are confined to this one source file."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2165,"cache_read_input_tokens":154937,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2165},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9e10c5bb-b262-42b1-82a9-825bdddbbe96","uuid":"80496b9b-984b-40aa-ac93-9502bee0278e","request_id":"req_011CcZzA47k69rVBRgyoYc7t"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":1375123,"duration_api_ms":1370928,"ttft_ms":4056,"ttft_stream_ms":4053,"time_to_request_ms":1186,"num_turns":44,"result":"I've applied the remediation. Here's a summary of my analysis and the fix.\n\n## What FINDING.txt described\nA CWE-200 Information Exposure vulnerability in `Redirect30xInterceptor.java`, spanning the header-name imports (41-46), the credential-strip decision in `exitAfterHandlingRedirect` (113-119), and the header-removal block in `propagatedHeaders` (209-216).\n\n## What I verified\nI traced the full redirect data flow exhaustively (the interceptor, `Uri.isSameBase`, `NettyRequestSender`, `NettyRequestFactory`, `NettyResponseFuture`):\n\n- `stripAuth = !sameBase || schemeDowngrade || stripAuthorizationOnRedirect` is `true` for **every** cross-origin or scheme-downgrade redirect.\n- When stripping, the code removes the `Authorization` and `Proxy-Authorization` headers in `propagatedHeaders`, nulls the realm on the new `RequestBuilder`, and nulls `future.setRealm(null)`/`future.setProxyRealm(null)` — so realm-based credential regeneration in `NettyRequestFactory` is also prevented.\n\nThat credential path is sound — it can only over-strip, never leak. The residual gap is that `propagatedHeaders` copies **all other** request headers to the redirect target, and the one credential-bearing header it failed to remove is **`Cookie`**. On a cross-origin or HTTPS→HTTP downgrade redirect, a request's `Cookie` header (session credentials) was forwarded to the new target — the CWE-200 exposure, in exactly the flagged regions.\n\n## The fix\nIn `propagatedHeaders`, when `stripAuthorization` is set (cross-origin / scheme-downgrade / configured), the `Cookie` header is now removed alongside `Authorization`/`Proxy-Authorization`, plus the `COOKIE` header-name import.\n\n## Why behavior is preserved\n- **Same-origin** redirects (`stripAuthorization == false`) are untouched — cookies and auth still flow as before.\n- Cookies legitimately scoped to the **new** target are still attached afterward via the `CookieStore` lookup (`cookieStore.get(newUri)` → re-encoded at write time), so only the leaked, cross-origin-inherited `Cookie` header is dropped.\n- Existing redirect tests are same-origin, and cookie tests use `addCookie` (which flows through `request.getCookies()`, not the raw header), so none are affected.\n\nNo build/commit was performed (offline maven can't resolve dependencies here), and changes are confined to this one source file.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"9e10c5bb-b262-42b1-82a9-825bdddbbe96","total_cost_usd":5.822241000000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":3323,"cache_creation_input_tokens":142945,"cache_read_input_tokens":3629980,"output_tokens":102420,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":142945,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1396,"cache_read_input_tokens":154937,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2165,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2165},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":606,"outputTokens":16,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.000686,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-8":{"inputTokens":3323,"outputTokens":102420,"cacheReadInputTokens":3629980,"cacheCreationInputTokens":142945,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":5.821555000000001,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01UwDQFMNbujS1rnBGukJXHN","tool_input":{"command":"curl -sI --max-time 10 https://raw.githubusercontent.com 2>&1 | head -3 || echo \"NO NET\""}}],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"7adacd64-ad7f-4f6